From 820901a7f007be990ce624773106113844ffe70f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Sun, 10 May 2026 13:51:30 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 106/174] alpha: entry.S non-strace path saves syscall nr to
 regs->r1/r2
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Commit 55b22075f7840 ("alpha: add support for SECCOMP and SECCOMP_FILTER")
reworked entSys to consistently track the syscall state in regs->r1
(current/mutable) and regs->r2 (original, preserved for restart).  It
correctly populates both slots in the strace path (after
syscall_trace_enter returns the possibly-modified nr) but the
non-strace fast path -- the common case -- doesn't set them at all.
sp+8 and sp+16 retain whatever PAL entry left in $1/$2.

The syscall return path then loads $18 from sp+16 in $syscall_error
to thread the original syscall nr through ret_from_sys_call →
do_work_pending → do_signal as the C `r0` parameter.  When that
loaded value happens to be zero (the common case if $2 was zero at
PAL entry), do_signal()'s `if (r0)` guard skips the ERESTART
restart/EINTR conversion entirely and ERESTARTSYS=512 leaks straight
to userspace's errno on every signal-interrupted syscall.

Reproduced on alpha LTP: every test that uses SAFE_WAITPID after the
test framework installs SIGALRM/SIGINT/SIGTERM/SIGUSR1 handlers
TBROK'd with "waitpid(N,...) failed: 512 (512)" and a kernel without
this fix runs alpha LTP at 19p/55f/27s instead of the expected
73p/1f/27s.

Fix: in entSys, after SAVE_ALL, also store $0 (the PAL-provided
syscall nr) into regs->r1 (sp+8) and regs->r2 (sp+16) BEFORE the
strace branch, so both paths see the right values.  The strace path
still updates sp+8 from syscall_trace_enter's return; sp+16 retains
the original nr for restart, exactly as the seccomp commit's
comments promised.

After this fix:
  alpha PGCL=4: LTP 74p/0f/27s
  alpha PGCL=6: LTP 73p/1f/27s

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 arch/alpha/kernel/entry.S | 11 +++++++++++
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/alpha/kernel/entry.S b/arch/alpha/kernel/entry.S
index 09c9042abde4..65fb010ad7cf 100644
--- a/arch/alpha/kernel/entry.S
+++ b/arch/alpha/kernel/entry.S
@@ -549,6 +549,17 @@ entSys:
 	stq	$17, SP_OFF+32($sp)
 	s8addq	$0, $5, $5
 	stq	$18, SP_OFF+40($sp)
+	/* Save the syscall number into regs->r1 (mutable) and regs->r2
+	 * (preserved for restart).  Without this the strace path sets
+	 * regs->r1 itself but the non-strace fast path leaves both slots
+	 * holding whatever PAL entry put in $1/$2 -- garbage from the
+	 * caller's perspective.  $syscall_error then loads $18 from
+	 * regs->r2 to drive ERESTART restart, and the garbage value
+	 * (often zero) suppresses do_signal()'s `if (r0)` ERESTART
+	 * conversion, leaking ERESTARTSYS=512 into userspace errno.
+	 */
+	stq	$0, 8($sp)		/* regs->r1 = current syscall nr */
+	stq	$0, 16($sp)		/* regs->r2 = original syscall nr */
 	.cfi_rel_offset	$16, SP_OFF+24
 	.cfi_rel_offset	$17, SP_OFF+32
 	.cfi_rel_offset	$18, SP_OFF+40
-- 
